Here, a few remarks on the above-mentioned pressure resolution are made. Since boundary conditions for the pressure equation, which are mentioned below, can be regarded as Neumann type, we have one choice to determine an absolute value of pressure. This implies that the matrix generated by the discretized Laplacian L in Eq. (12) is not of full rank. However, it is possible to uniquely determine the pressure field by the present iteration with the prescribed initial step. Such an iteration procedure corresponds to a discrete stepwise algorithm for a parabolic equation with initial and Neumann boundary conditions. Existence and uniqueness of solutions for such a parabolic equation, with suitable conditions, are known in the theory of partial differential equation; its steady-state solution satisfies the original Poisson equation.

